title: Leaves from the journal of our life in the Highlands, from 1848 to 1861 :
author: Victoria
snippet: We started about ten minutes past eleven,and proceeded exactly as last year, fording theGeldie at first very frequently.

title: Leaves from the journal of our life in the Highlands, from 1848 to 1861 :
author: Victoria
snippet: The Fishie and Geldie rise almoston a level, with very little distance betweenthem.

title: Leaves from the journal of our life in the Highlands, from 1848 to 1861 :
author: Victoria
snippet: We mounted at once, and rode up along the Geldie,which we had to ford frequently to avoid the bogs,and rode on for two hours up Glen Geldie, overa moor which was so soft and boggy in places,that we had to get off several times.

title: Leaves from the journal of our life in the Highlands, from 1848 to 1861 :
author: Victoria
snippet: We went on five milesbeyond the Linn of Dee, to the Shepherd's Shielof Geldie, or, properly speaking, Giuly, where wefound our ponies and a guide,* Charlie Stewart.
